{Back in March 2023, I spoke to Geert van der Velde, the Chessable CEO, about what my next course should be about. He said 'King's Indian Attack!'. I asked why, as I had opening specialties I could work on. He answered me 'People love the KIA! Trust me, you wanna do the KIA!'. I started my work from zero and discovered the incredible richness of the 1. Nf3 and 2. g3 move order. Unlike in a typical Reti, we do not commit to an early c4. Depending on how Black plays, we might go d3-e4, d4, or c4. The huge majority of positions are unexplored and I discovered an incredible number of ideas. I've worked on the course for several months and time has been flying. After finishing the ChessBase files I decided to try the KIA myself. After three years of bad results, I beat the previous French Champion Jules Moussard in my first KIA game, using a novelty I found while working in the Chessable office in Barcelona! I continued with the same opening all the coming games and it came to a result of +7 =3 -0 in the following ten games! Being able to vary our plans depending on Black's moves, we can sometimes transpose into favorable 1. c4 or 1. d4 openings. Most positions are hard-fighting ones and I believe there's room to really outplay a bunch of players thanks to the new ideas provided in the course. My own games are the proof of that! I really enjoyed working on this repertoire, covering all possibilities by Black, but most importantly, exploring unknown territories. I hope you'll enjoy my work and will score many points as well! Romain Édouard} 1. Z0 *

