1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O O-O 5. c4 d5 {Black opens the position, going for a Grunfeld-type pawn structure.} 6. cxd5 Nxd5 7. d4 $1 {We've reached a favorable version of the g3-Grunfeld.} Nb6 8. Nc3 ({I've tried to make} 8. Nbd2 $5 {work but didn't end up satisfied, e.g.} Nc6 9. Nb3 $146 a5 $5 10. a4 Be6 $5 {Forcing the events. Of course, this is just a variation out of many possible:} 11. Nc5 Nxd4 12. Nxd4 Qxd4 13. Qxd4 Bxd4 14. Nxe6 fxe6 15. Bxb7 Rab8 16. Ba6 Nd5 17. Bb5 c6 18. Bxc6 Bxb2 19. Rb1 Bxc1 20. Rbxc1 Rb4 {with a likely draw.}) 8... Nc6 9. d5 $5 (9. e3 {would transpose into the mainstream Grunfeld with g3 - 1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 g6 3.g3 Bg7 4.Bg2 d5 5.cxd5 Nxd5 6.Nf3 Nb6! 7.Nc3 Nc6 8.e3 O-O 9.O-O . But with the move order we used, we didn't have to push e3.}) 9... Na5 10. e4 (10. Qc2 {is the alternative but after} c6 11. dxc6 Nxc6 12. Rd1 Qe8 {I could not find anything for White. The proposed alternative challenges Black a lot, as he has to find lots of strong moves in order to survive.}) 10... c6 11. Bf4 {Again one line of many, but the trickiest one to handle for Black in my opinion.} Bxc3 $5 {Lately it's been understood that if Black doesn't take the pawn, he is simply worse.} 12. bxc3 cxd5 13. exd5 Qxd5 14. Nd4 $1 ({I believe this is the most dangerous move.} 14. Qe2 Qc4 {has been played twice by GM Shevchenko (as Black). He scored two wins. The idea is that Qxe7 is always met with ...Nd5.}) 14... Qc5 15. Re1 (15. Nb3 {is less threatening as we will see in the main course.}) 15... Bd7 $1 {For concrete reasons, this move is best. It is probably related to the fact that it develops Black's last undeveloped piece!} 16. Re5 Qa3 17. Bc1 $146 {An interesting new idea in a position that, so far, is known to be a forced draw.} Qxc3 18. Bh6 {Here Black has several ways to draw, but one must focus on how many moves he has at his disposal and how many chances he has to miss. My personal bet is that this position is a good practical choice. In the chapter, we will explore this line [/variation/31706284] in more detail.} *

