1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 c5 {This is the start of one of the best lines for Black.} 3. Bg2 Nc6 4. d4 ({We go for a reversed Grunfeld.} 4. O-O e5 5. d3 {would be a reversed King's Indian, but I simply did not like it from the White side. Only having to equalize (while White tries to be better against the King's Indian) gives Black too many possibilities to play and obtain a reasonable position.}) 4... Nf6 5. O-O e6 6. c4 dxc4 7. dxc5 ({The alternatives are} 7. Ne5 {and}) (7. Qa4 {, but they're known to be fine for Black.}) 7... Qxd1 8. Rxd1 Bxc5 {We've transposed into a main line of the Catalan.} 9. Nfd2 $5 ({This move has become popular some years ago, instead of the traditional} 9. Nbd2 c3 {line. However, since then, solutions have been found for Black to make a draw. Nevertheless, I would like to suggest that line which is really not easy to play for Black over the board, especially if he has transposed into this line somehow accidentally.}) 9... Na5 $1 {The best move.} 10. Na3 Bxa3 11. bxa3 {It took quite some time even for top GMs to find equality for Black here, but it seems to exist few solutions if he is extremely precise. Black also has many ways to go wrong!} O-O (11... Nd5 12. Ne4 O-O {transposes.}) 12. Ne4 (12. Bb2 Nd5 13. Rac1 b5 14. Ne4 Bb7 {Tricky. 14...a6!? $146 with the idea of meeting Nd6 or Nc5 with ...Nb7 should be fine as well. Anyway, after the following more or less forced sequence, Black seemed fine as well.} 15. Nd6 Bc6 16. Bxd5 exd5 17. Bc3 Nb7 18. Nf5 Rfe8 $1 19. Nxg7 Rxe2 20. Nf5 Re6 21. Nd4 Nc5 $1 {= $13 Vidit - Aronian, chess24.com 2021. Black's knight (and central pawns after a capture on e6 ) give him enough compensation.}) 12... Nd5 $1 {One of the paths to equality.} 13. Bd2 b6 $1 {The most precise.} 14. Rac1 (14. Nc3 {trades too many pieces as well:} Bb7 15. Nxd5 Bxd5 16. Bxa5 bxa5 17. Bxd5 exd5 18. Rxd5 Rfc8 {followed by ...Rab8 with a highly likely draw: Vitiugov - Esipenko, Moscow 2021.}) 14... Ba6 15. Bxa5 bxa5 16. Nc5 Bb5 17. Bxd5 exd5 18. Rxd5 Z0 ({This is highly unpleasant for Black; after} 18... Rfd8 19. Rxd8+ Rxd8 20. Ne4 f5 21. Nc3 Bc6 22. f3 $14 {although there's some work ahead, is a one-way street for White: Carlsen - Harikrishna, Riyadh 2017.}) *

