1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 c6 4. O-O Nbd7 {This is not a line to worry about.} 5. d4 e6 6. Nbd2 Be7 $1 7. c4 (7. Re1 O-O 8. e4 dxe4 9. Nxe4 Nxe4 10. Rxe4 b6 {would no longer be convincing for White: Black is in time to play ...Bb7 and ...c5.}) 7... O-O 8. Qc2 {We got an advantageous Catalan as Black has played …Nbd7 too early, and we will be able to push e2-e4 in wonderful conditions.} b6 9. e4 dxe4 10. Nxe4 {This just gives Black poor and passive positions.} Bb7 (10... Nxe4 11. Qxe4 Bb7 12. Rd1 Nf6 13. Qe2 $16) 11. Rd1 Qc8 12. Nxf6+ Nxf6 13. c5 Nd5 14. Bg5 $16 {Black is suffering from a lack of space, and may pay a high price for his hole on d6. Andreikin - Omelja, chess.com 2022.} *

