1. Nf3 f5 {Black plays in the spirit of the Dutch Defense. We will try to take advantage of the fact that white has yet to play d4.} 2. d3 $5 {White wants to play e4 which is very different to the main lines of the Dutch Defence where white is already committed to d4.} d6 $5 {Black also intends to fight for the center.} 3. e4 $1 e5 4. Nc3 $1 Nc6 {The only playable line.} 5. exf5 Bxf5 $6 {This simple recapture isn’t good. As we’ll see, Black needs to be more ingenious if he wants a playable game.} 6. d4 $1 {White takes over the initiative.} Nxd4 (6... Nb4 $6 7. Bb5+ c6 8. Ba4 $16 {White simply defends the c2-pawn and the black knight feels very lonely on b4.}) (6... e4 $6 7. d5 exf3 8. dxc6 bxc6 9. Qxf3 $16 {and White enjoys a nice advantage.}) 7. Nxd4 exd4 8. Qxd4 c6 {The only playable move, but the position is already very dubious.} 9. g4 $146 Bxc2 (9... Be6 10. Be3 Nf6 $6 11. g5 Nd5 12. O-O-O {with excellent prospects for White as Black is underdeveloped.}) 10. Bg2 $1 Qf6 (10... Nf6 11. O-O Be7 12. g5 $1 Nh5 13. Bf3 $16) 11. Qc4 {Again, Black has concrete problems.} d5 (11... Ne7 12. O-O d5 13. Qe2 Bg6 14. f4 O-O-O 15. f5 Bf7 16. Bf4 $16) (11... O-O-O 12. Bxc6 $1 bxc6 $6 13. Qxc6+ Kb8 14. Be3) 12. Nxd5 cxd5 13. Qxc2 Bb4+ 14. Kf1 {White's king is uncastled, but still safer than Black's!} *

