1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O O-O 5. c4 d5 {Black opens the position, going for a Grunfeld-type pawn structure.} 6. cxd5 Nxd5 7. d4 $1 {We've reached a favorable version of the g3-Grunfeld. After 1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 g6 3.g3 Bg7 4.Bg2 d5 5.cxd5 Nxd5 6.Nf3 it is known that 6...Nb6 (with the idea of 7.Nc3 Nc6 , provoking 8.e3 , and only now 8...O-O ) is more precise than 6... O-O.} c5 $6 {A try to go for a totally symmetrical position, but known as too slow. White has two interesting ways to play.} 8. e4 {Logical. Whites takes an edge in the center.} Nf6 $1 {The most resourceful: White needs to do something in the center.} (8... Nb6 $2 9. d5 e6 10. Bg5 Qd7 11. Nc3 {would be awful for Black, who is undeveloped.}) 9. e5 {Now Black has two possibilities, and both should hold with incredibly precise play. Again White has two options, and against both Black will suffer to keep a playable position.} Nfd7 10. e6 (10. d5 $5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Bxe5 12. Nc3 Nd7 13. Re1 {offers White great compensation. Whenever Black goes ...Bg7 White goes Bf4. However, after something like} Re8 14. a4 a6 15. Bg5 Bd6 16. Ne4 f6 17. Be3 b6 {it is unclear how big is White compensation, though he is definitely not worse.}) 10... fxe6 11. Ng5 Nf6 12. Qe1 (12. dxc5 $5 Qxd1 13. Rxd1 Nc6 14. Nc3 h6 15. Nge4 Nd5 {and even after a move like} 16. h4 $5 {Black's position is unpleasant to defend.}) 12... Nc6 $1 (12... cxd4 $2 13. Nxe6 Bxe6 14. Qxe6+ Kh8 15. Bxb7) 13. Nxe6 Bxe6 14. Qxe6+ Kh8 15. Bxc6 (15. dxc5 Nd4 16. Qc4 b5 $1 17. Qd3 {17.cxb6 Rc8 18.Qa6 Qxb6 19.Qxb6 Ne2+ 20.Kh1 axb6 21.Nc3 Nxc3 22.bxc3 Rxc3= Black is active enough to hold a draw.} Rc8 {and Black has fine counterplay - I could not find anything for White despite trying with the strongest engines. Nevertheless, note how precise Black had to be till here...}) 15... bxc6 16. dxc5 Qd5 17. Qe2 Ne4 $5 (17... Qxc5 18. Nc3 $14) 18. Nc3 (18. Be3 Ng5 $1 19. Bxg5 Qxg5 20. Nc3 Qxc5 21. Rac1 a5 {and Black should be active enough to draw this, though he is of course sitting on the unpleasant side of the board.}) 18... Nxc3 19. bxc3 Bxc3 20. Rd1 Qf5 $5 (20... Qxc5 {allows} 21. Rb1 $1 {with good compensation.}) 21. Bb2 Bxb2 22. Qxb2+ {And after 22...Kg8 followed by ...Rad8, Black should be able to draw.} *

