1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O O-O 5. c4 d5 {Black opens the position, going for a Grunfeld-type pawn structure.} 6. cxd5 Nxd5 7. d4 $1 {We've reached a favorable version of the g3-Grunfeld. After 1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 g6 3.g3 Bg7 4.Bg2 d5 5.cxd5 Nxd5 6.Nf3 it is known that 6...Nb6 (with the idea of 7.Nc3 Nc6 , provoking 8.e3 , and only now 8...O-O ) is more precise than 6... O-O.} Nb6 8. Nc3 ({I've tried to make} 8. Nbd2 $5 {work but didn't end up satisfied, e.g.} Nc6 9. Nb3 $146 a5 $5 10. a4 Be6 $5 {Forcing the events. Of course, this is just a variation out of many possible:} 11. Nc5 Nxd4 12. Nxd4 Qxd4 13. Qxd4 Bxd4 14. Nxe6 fxe6 15. Bxb7 Rab8 16. Ba6 Nd5 17. Bb5 c6 18. Bxc6 Bxb2 19. Rb1 Bxc1 20. Rbxc1 Rb4 {with a likely draw.}) 8... Nc6 9. d5 $5 (9. e3 {would transpose into the mainstream Grunfeld with g3 - 1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 g6 3.g3 Bg7 4.Bg2 d5 5.cxd5 Nxd5 6.Nf3 Nb6! 7.Nc3 Nc6 8.e3 O-O 9.O-O . But with the move order we used, we didn't have to push e3.}) 9... Na5 10. e4 (10. Qc2 {is the alternative but after} c6 11. dxc6 Nxc6 12. Rd1 Qe8 {I could not find anything for White. The proposed alternative challenges Black a lot, as he has to find lots of strong moves in order to survive.}) 10... c6 11. Bf4 {Again one line of many, but the trickiest one to handle for Black in my opinion.} cxd5 12. Nxd5 Nxd5 13. exd5 Nc4 (13... Bd7 $2 14. Rc1 Rc8 15. b3 b6 16. Ne5 Rxc1 17. Qxc1 {1-0 Vachier Lagrave - Kovalev, Dubai 2014.}) 14. Rc1 $1 ({The best move order.} 14. Qb3 Nd6 15. Rfe1 Bf5 16. Be5 {might be enough for a small advantage too: ½-½ Vachier Lagrave - Nepomniachtchi, Moscow 2010.}) ({After} 14. b3 Nb6 15. d6 Bxa1 $5 {I am not convinced White has anything at all. 15...exd6 16.Rc1 transposes to 14. Rc1.} 16. dxe7 {16.Qxa1 f6 $132} Qxe7 17. Qxa1 {17.Bd6 Qd8 18.Bxf8 Qxd1 19.Rxd1 Kxf8 20.Rxa1 a5=} f6 18. Re1 Qf7 19. Bd6 Rd8 20. Re7 Qf8 21. Rd7 Qe8 {with a draw.}) 14... Nxb2 15. Qd2 b5 16. Ne5 $1 {The point!} Nc4 (16... Bxe5 $2 17. Bxe5 Nc4 18. Rxc4 $1 bxc4 19. d6 $1 {+-}) 17. Nxc4 bxc4 18. d6 Z0 ({And after} 18... Be6 19. Bxa8 Qxa8 20. dxe7 Re8 21. Rfd1 Rxe7 22. Qd8+ Re8 23. Qxa8 Rxa8 24. Bd2 {with the idea of Bc3, Black has a very long day ahead.}) *

