7. Rfxd4 Qxd4 28. Rxd4 Rxd4 29. Qe5 Rd3 30. Qxa5 {with a highly unpleasant position for Black.}) (22... Bc6 $2 23. Rxe7 Bxg2 24. Re1 $1 Nd7 {Preventing Qe8+.} 25. Nb5 Qf6 26. Kxg2 Nf8 27. Nc7 Nc6 28. Re4 Nd4 29. Rxd4 Qxd4 30. Nxa8 Qd5+ 31. Kg1 {Black's position is very dubious due to his dark-squares problems.}) 23. Rd3 $1 Rac8 24. Rxe7 Z0 ({Now a forced line starts where Black does not completely survive.} 24... Nd5 25. Bxd5 Qxd5 26. Re5 Qc4 27. Rxa5 Rxd4 28. Qe5 Qc1+ 29. Kg2 $1 {29.Bxc1 Rxc1+ 30.Kg2 Bc6+ 31.Rf3 Rd3 is much less clear.} Bc6+ 30. f3 Qxh6 31. Qxd4 {with a clear advantage for White.}) *

