eat compensation.}) (22... e5 $6 23. Nf3 {is problematic for Black.}) 23. Bxb7 Z0 ({Now Black can hold if he finds a series of only moves - and not many of them are easy!} 23... Rc7 24. Ba6 Re8 25. Nf3 Bb5 26. Bxb5 Qxb5 27. a4 $5 Qxa4 28. Ne5 Qb5 $1 {28. ..Rec8?! 29.Rd4 Qb5 30.Qd3 Nxe5 31.Rd8+ Qe8 32.Rxe8+ Rxe8 33.Qb5 Rxc1+ 34.Bxc1 and Black is there to sit for long.} 29. Nxc4 Rec8 30. Re4 Rxc4 {30...Qh5 31.Qd2 g5! 32.Qxg5+ Qxg5 33.Bxg5 f6 34.Nxb6 Rxc1+ 35.Bxc1 Rxc1+ 36.Kg2 axb6 37.Rxe7 is a bit annoying for Black, but a draw.} 31. Rexc4 Nxc4 32. Qxe7 Re8 33. Qf6 Qe5 {Black has avoided all the tricks and gets his well-deserved half-point!}) *

