1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O O-O (4... d5 5. c4 c6 6. b3 {would transpose to the mainline.}) 5. c4 c6 {A solid approach: consolidating the center before pushing ...d5.} 6. b3 Ne4 {It may look tempting, but it just forces d2-d4 that White was gonna play anyway.} 7. d4 d5 8. Bb2 {Here Black has many moves but I believe after any of them, White gets an easier position. I do not see ...Ne4 as an improvement of Black's position either.} a5 {The most fashionable move lately, and perhaps the most sensible one as well, is going for quick counterplay. Black wants to gain space and, if possible, disturb White's pieces with ...a4.} 9. Ne5 $5 {A completely new idea (together with the next move), which I find very interesting for White. The reason why I looked for this kind of idea is that the main lines were leading straight into boring positions.} (9. e3 {The most classical way to play (or}) (9. Nc3 {which transposes after} Bf5 10. e3 {Nxe3 ) . My problem here is that after the main moves 9...Bf5 10.Nc3 Nxc3 11.Bxc3 Be4 12.Bh3! 12.Qe2 is probably better but it again slows down White's play. At some point, Black will take on f3 when he has to (e.g. after Rfc1 and Bh3) and his position will be extremely solid. Instead, 12.Bh3 is supposed to accelerate the process but I believe it faces a concrete problem. 12...c5! followed by ...Nc6 or ... cxd4 and there is absolutely zero advantage for White.}) 9... Nd7 10. Na3 {Same as above. White wants to have the b5-square under control without giving Black a chance to trade knights on c3. Here we are happy that Black has slowed down his counterplay not pushing ..a4.} Qb6 (10... a4 11. b4 {is just a positive change of the pawn structure for White, who gains extra space. 10. ..Nxe5 11.dxe5 Be6 12.Rc1 is nice for White as well.}) 11. e3 a4 12. Nd3 axb3 13. axb3 Ndf6 14. f3 {This is the whole idea of moving the knight to d3: making f3 possible while still controlling the center.} Ng5 15. h4 $5 {Time to gain space on the kingside.} Ne6 16. g4 {And White has a very fun game ahead, and the advantage.} *

