1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O O-O (4... d5 5. c4 c6 6. b3 {would transpose to the mainline.}) 5. c4 c6 {A solid approach: consolidating the center before pushing ...d5.} 6. b3 d5 7. Bb2 {We are at a crossroads where Black has many possible moves, though White's plans do not change that much anyhow.} a5 {Here White has two very reliable options: playing it simple, ignoring a5, or playing 8. Nc3 which is a typical reaction to ...a5.} 8. Nc3 $5 Na6 (8... Re8 9. d4 Bf5 10. Ne5 Ne4 11. f4 $5 Nxc3 12. Bxc3 a4 13. e3 b5 14. cxd5 cxd5 15. Rc1 {was good for White in Anton Guijarro - Bortnyk, chess. com 2022, 0-1, although in the end Bortnyk's amazing blitz skills prevailed.}) 9. d4 $5 Ne4 10. Rc1 Bf5 11. e3 Nxc3 12. Bxc3 Be4 13. Qe2 {This is just a strange mixture of several lines for Black: there the knight should be on d7, ready to possibly come to f6, accompanied by a solid ...e6.} *

