1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O O-O (4... d5 5. c4 c6 6. b3 {would transpose to the mainline.}) 5. c4 c6 {A solid approach: consolidating the center before pushing ...d5.} 6. b3 d5 7. Bb2 {We are at a crossroads where Black has many possible moves, though White's plans do not change that much anyhow.} b5 8. Qc2 $5 ({Here I hesitated a long time between} 8. Qc2 {,}) (8. Nc3 {and}) (8. d3 {. But after the two latest Black trades everything on c4 and is close to equality. My choice went to 8. Qc2, with the simple idea to go d3 and Nbd2.}) 8... bxc4 (8... a5 9. d3 Qb6 10. Nbd2 $14 {is similar: White just sits on the pleasant side of the board.}) 9. bxc4 Nbd7 10. d3 Re8 11. Ne5 $5 {Preventing ... e5.} Nxe5 12. Bxe5 {And White's position is pleasant, once again. The b1-knight may develop either on d2 or c3, for a change.} *

