1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O O-O (4... d5 5. c4 c6 6. b3 {would transpose to the mainline.}) 5. c4 c6 {A solid approach: consolidating the center before pushing ...d5.} 6. b3 d5 7. Bb2 {We are at a crossroads where Black has many possible moves, though White's plans do not change that much anyhow.} dxc4 $6 8. bxc4 c5 {Black changes the pawn structure completely: but it is not a positive change. Now White has a majority in the center.} (8... Qb6 9. Qc1 Bf5 10. d3 Na6 11. Nc3 $16 {Black's pieces are misplaced: they have no target: 1-0 Harsha - Nayan Kumar, Dhaka 2022.}) 9. d3 Nc6 (9... a6 10. Nbd2 b5 11. a4 b4 12. Nb3 {would just give Black an extra weakness on c5.}) (9... Qb6 10. Qc1 Nc6 11. Nc3 Bg4 12. Rb1 {is also clearly better for White.}) 10. Ne5 {And White's position is gonna be a dream.} *

