1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 c5 3. Bg2 Nc6 4. d4 ({This is a good line for Black, with precise play. Besides the main line (} 4. d4 {), I tried to analyze other things (}) (4. c4 {,}) (4. O-O e5 5. c4 {,}) (4. O-O e5 5. e4 {) but discarded all these options (except the last one, which I offer as an alternative at the end of the chapter) although you can find a summary of them below.}) ({Another possible line is} 4. c4 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Nc3 Nc7 7. O-O e5 8. d3 Be7 9. Nd2 {but I do not really like it for White. A possible follow-up would be} Be6 10. Nc4 Nd5 11. Qb3 Nd4 $1 12. Qxb7 Rb8 13. Qxa7 Ra8 14. Qb7 {with a draw.}) 4... cxd4 5. Nxd4 Qb6 $5 {Not a bad line at all. In fact, White is able to put pressure, but with exact play Black should manage to hold.} 6. Nb3 d5 {This is definitely critical. Black should try to take the center.} 7. O-O e6 8. Nc3 {I've tried several things and came to the conclusion that this was the best practical try. Black really struggles to equalize.} Be7 9. a4 $1 O-O 10. a5 {Gaining space before breaking the center.} Qd8 11. e4 $5 {It is time to open the center and the long diagonal for our g2 bishop.} d4 12. e5 $1 dxc3 13. exf6 Bxf6 14. bxc3 {The last sequence of moves was forced, and now Black has a choice. This is something we like: the more choices, the more time your opponent will spend and the more chances he has to go wrong!} Qxd1 {It is time to check what happens after the queen exchange.} 15. Rxd1 Bxc3 16. Ra4 {Our typical rook lift in this line, the rook can be quickly transferred through c4 to c7 in the black field.} a6 {Black should parry a5-a6.} 17. Be3 Rd8 18. Rb1 e5 {Black needs to activate his c8-bishop.} 19. Bb6 Bf5 $1 ({Active defense is best, as} 19... Rf8 $4 20. Bxc6 bxc6 21. Rc4 Bd4 22. c3 $1 {just wins.}) (19... Rd6 20. Rc4 Bd4 21. Bxc6 $5 Rxc6 22. Rxc6 bxc6 23. Bxd4 exd4 24. Nxd4 c5 25. Nc6 {with the rook coming to b6 seems no fun for Black.}) 20. Bxd8 ({We can also initiate an interesting tactical operation such as} 20. Bxc6 bxc6 21. Rc4 Bxc2 22. Rf1 Bxb3 23. Rxc3 Ba4 24. Bxd8 Rxd8 {is just equal.}) 20... Bxc2 21. Bb6 Bxb1 22. Nc5 Bb4 $1 23. Nxb7 e4 24. Nd8 Nxd8 25. Rxb4 Z0 ({We are at the end of training line, however after} 25... Bd3 26. Bxe4 Bxe4 27. Rxe4 Nc6 {Black should be able to make a draw without much difficulty. It can happen, if Black plays all the best moves.}) *

