1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 b5 {A move Black sometimes plays when it's kind of clear that White's light-squared bishop will move to g2, thus not attacking the b5-pawn. Black gains spaces on the queenside and allows a vis-à-vis with the g2-bishop, more actively than with 1... b6.} (2... d6 3. Bg2 e5 4. O-O {followed by c4, Nc3, will be a good version for White of lines we've seen earlier or will see later.}) (2... e6 {will be followed by ...b6 or ...d5 and transpose into other chapters too.}) 3. Bg2 Bb7 4. d3 {As against ...b6 ideas we've seen, this seems to be the most logical to face ...Bb7. White will close the bishop's diagonal with e2-e4 unless Black closes it himself with ...d7-d5.} ({I remember a brilliant victory by Magnus over MVL after} 4. Na3 {when after} a6 5. c4 {Black played} b4 {. However, after 5...e6 ( 5...e5!? also makes sense.) 6.b3 bxc4 7.Nxc4 a5 8.O-O d5!? it looks to me like Black is somehow okay: 9.Nfxe5 c6 10.Nb2 Nfd7 11.Nxd7 Nxd7 with relatively easy play for Black.}) 4... e6 (4... d5 $6 5. O-O e6 6. c4 {transposes to 1.Nf3 d5 2.g3 Nf6 3.Bg2 b5 4.O-O Bb7 5.d3 e6 6.c4 .}) 5. e4 d6 (5... Be7 {will soon transpose as ... d6 is probably next.}) 6. O-O c5 {The most logical move, fighting for the center.} 7. d4 $5 {One of the two best and most challenging moves.} Nxe4 {This goes into an amazing forced sequence.} 8. Ng5 d5 9. Nxe4 dxe4 10. dxc5 Bxc5 (10... Qxd1 $2 11. Rxd1 Bxc5 12. Nc3 {is much worse for Black than allowing White to take on d8.}) 11. Qxd8+ Kxd8 12. Nc3 f5 13. Nxb5 Nd7 14. Bg5+ Nf6 15. b4 $1 {An important move to enable Nd4!} Bxb4 ({Forced, as after} 15... Bb6 $2 16. c4 $16 {White has the advantage.}) 16. Nd4 {Not the only move, but the most enterprising.} Bc3 17. Nxe6+ Ke7 18. Nxg7 Bxa1 19. Rxa1 Z0 ({And after} 19... Kf7 $1 20. Nxf5 Kg6 $1 21. Bxf6 Kxf6 22. Nd6 Bc6 23. Bxe4 {White has very good alternatives, 23. c4 or 23. Nxe4.} Bxe4 24. Nxe4+ Kg6 25. Kg2 {White has three pawns for the exchange. Two of them are isolated, Black has fine chances to draw, but we're definitely happy with White here.}) *

