course,} 15... g6 $2 {loses to} 16. Qe5) 16. dxc5 Bd5 {The critical position. It seems Black holds but he should really be brave to enter this line against a well-prepared opponent!} 17. b4 $5 Z0 ({And after} 17... Qe8 18. Qe2 Kc8 19. Bxe4 Bxe4 20. Qxe4 Qc6 21. Qe2 Be7 22. Bf4 Rd8 {White has enough compensation, but probably nothing more. • Other moves don't work as well, for example 17.Rd1 Bxc5 18.Rxd5+ exd5 19.Qxd5+ Bd6 20.Bxe4 and White, it seems, has compensation for a draw - but not more as he doesn't have enough pieces left! • 17.Bh3 Kc6 18.Rd1 Bxc5 19.Bxe6 Bxe6 20.Rxd8 Rxd8 is OK for Black.}) *

