1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nc6 {Black wants to push ...e5. Of course, allowing it wouldn't necessarily be bad, it would be no less than some sort of reversed Pirc with an extra tempo. Nevertheless, with the black knight on c6 blocking Black's c-pawn, pushing d4 to prevent ...e5 is by far the most logical.} 3. d4 Bf5 ({Apart from} 3... Bg4 {, or}) (3... Nf6 {to transpose to ...Bf5 or ...Bg4 afterwards, other third moves don't really make sense.}) 4. Bg2 Nf6 5. O-O {White takes his time before playing the logical c4 so that the move ...Nb4 becomes less threatening.} e6 6. c4 Nb4 $2 {This is just bad.} 7. cxd5 (7. Nc3 $5 {is possible as well, with similar ideas.}) 7... exd5 (7... Nc2 8. Ne5 Nxa1 9. Qa4+ {is already a disaster for Black.}) 8. Nc3 Z0 ({And now only} 8... Nc2 {could justify Black's play but it loses to} 9. Nh4) *

