1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nc6 {Black wants to push ...e5. Of course, allowing it wouldn't necessarily be bad, it would be no less than some sort of reversed Pirc with an extra tempo. Nevertheless, with the black knight on c6 blocking Black's c-pawn, pushing d4 to prevent ...e5 is by far the most logical.} 3. d4 Bf5 ({Apart from} 3... Bg4 {, or}) (3... Nf6 {to transpose to ...Bf5 or ...Bg4 afterwards, other third moves don't really make sense.}) 4. Bg2 h6 {Black wants to have a safety square for his bishop on h7.} 5. O-O e6 6. c4 Nf6 {White has developed his kingside, and now it is time to take advantage of the tempi Black has lost.} 7. Nc3 (7. Ne5 $5 {is possible as well.}) 7... Be7 8. Ne5 O-O 9. cxd5 exd5 10. Bf4 {White is simply better, Black's knight is simply misplaced on c6. 1-0 Grischuk - Grachev, Moscow 2022.} *

