1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 c5 3. Bg2 Nc6 4. d4 ({We go for a reversed Grunfeld.} 4. O-O e5 5. d3 {would be a reversed King's Indian, but I simply did not like it from the White side. Only having to equalize (while White tries to be better against the King's Indian) gives Black too many possibilities to play and obtain a reasonable position.}) 4... e6 5. O-O cxd4 6. Nxd4 Bc5 7. Nb3 Bb6 (7... Be7 8. c4 Nf6 {transposes here [/variation/31872484/#/8/w].}) 8. c4 Nge7 (8... dxc4 $2 9. Qxd8+ Bxd8 10. N3d2 $16 {with an awful endgame for Black.}) (8... Nf6 {transposes here [/variation/31872484/#/8/w].}) 9. cxd5 exd5 ({An interesting option, played by Jorden van Voreest amongst others.} 9... Nxd5 {transposes.}) 10. Nc3 O-O $1 (10... d4 11. Na4 {would likely transpose as} Bc7 $2 12. e3 $1 {is definitely bad for Black: White's pieces are powerful.}) 11. Na4 (11. Nxd5 $6 Nxd5 12. Qxd5 Qxd5 13. Bxd5 Bg4 {with compensation for Black.}) 11... d4 12. Bd2 $5 ({I believe White should play calmly and not hurry to take the bishop pair. After} 12. Nxb6 axb6 13. e3 d3 $1 {Black was dynamic enough in Amin - Van Foreest, Almaty 2022, 1-0.}) 12... Re8 13. Nbc5 {White will follow up with b4, Rc1, and sits on the most pleasant side of the board: White won in the game Kilic -Gallana, Vrnjacka Banja 2023.} *

