1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 c5 {This is the start of one of the best lines for Black.} 3. Bg2 Nc6 4. d4 ({We go for a reversed Grunfeld.} 4. O-O e5 5. d3 {would be a reversed King's Indian, but I simply did not like it from the White side. Only having to equalize (while White tries to be better against the King's Indian) gives Black too many possibilities to play and obtain a reasonable position.}) 4... Nf6 5. O-O g6 $6 6. dxc5 $1 {Here we take the pawn!} Bg7 7. c3 O-O 8. b4 Ne4 9. a3 a5 10. Bb2 $1 {Best is to give the pawn back at once.} axb4 11. axb4 Rxa1 12. Bxa1 Nxb4 13. cxb4 Bxa1 14. Nd4 $1 {A key move, 'trapping' the bishop on a1.} Nf6 15. e3 Bg4 16. Qb3 $16 {At some point Black will take to take on d4 and White's majority on the queenside will be devastating: Rakhmanov - Cheparinov, Turkey 2016.} *

