1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 c5 {This is the start of one of the best lines for Black.} 3. Bg2 Nc6 4. d4 ({We go for a reversed Grunfeld.} 4. O-O e5 5. d3 {would be a reversed King's Indian, but I simply did not like it from the White side. Only having to equalize (while White tries to be better against the King's Indian) gives Black too many possibilities to play and obtain a reasonable position.}) 4... Nf6 5. O-O e6 (5... cxd4 6. Nxd4 e5 {6...e6 7.c4 transposes to 1.Nf3 Nf6 2.g3 c5 3.Bg2 Nc6 4.d4 cxd4 5.Nxd4 d5 6.c4 e6} 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. c4 {transposes to 1.Nf3 Nf6 2.g3 c5 3.Bg2 Nc6 4.d4 cxd4 5.Nxd4 d5 6.c4 e5 etc.}) 6. c4 dxc4 7. dxc5 ({The alternatives are} 7. Ne5 {and}) (7. Qa4 {, but they're known to be fine for Black.}) 7... Qxd1 8. Rxd1 Bxc5 {We've transposed into a main line of the Catalan.} 9. Nfd2 $5 ({This move has become popular some years ago, instead of the traditional} 9. Nbd2 c3 {line. However, since then, solutions have been found for Black to make a draw. Nevertheless, I would like to suggest that line which is really not easy to play for Black over the board, especially if he has transposed into this line somehow accidentally.}) 9... Ne5 $2 {Leads to a bad endgame.} 10. Na3 c3 11. bxc3 O-O 12. Nb3 $146 Be7 (12... Bb6 13. c4 Ned7 14. Nb5 Nc5 15. Ba3 {Heberla - Nisavic, Bassano del Grappa 2022.}) 13. Na5 $16 (13. c4 {was also good for White in Chigaev - Khamdamova, chess.com 2022.}) *

