4. Rac1 (14. Nc3 {trades too many pieces as well:} Bb7 15. Nxd5 Bxd5 16. Bxa5 bxa5 17. Bxd5 exd5 18. Rxd5 Rfc8 {followed by ...Rab8 with a highly likely draw: Vitiugov - Esipenko, Moscow 2021.}) 14... Ba6 15. Bxa5 bxa5 16. Nc5 Bb5 17. Bxd5 exd5 18. Rxd5 Z0 ({This is highly unpleasant for Black; after} 18... Rfd8 19. Rxd8+ Rxd8 20. Ne4 f5 21. Nc3 Bc6 22. f3 $14 {although there's some work ahead, is a one-way street for White: Carlsen - Harikrishna, Riyadh 2017.}) *

