1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 c5 {This is the start of one of the best lines for Black.} 3. Bg2 Nc6 4. d4 {We go for a reversed Grunfeld. 4.O-O e5 5.d3 would be a reversed King's Indian, but I simply did not like it from the White side. Only having to equalize (while White tries to be better against the King's Indian) gives Black too many possibilities to play and obtain a reasonable position.} Nf6 5. O-O e6 6. c4 Be7 {Black wants to transpose to a Tarrasch Opening.} 7. cxd5 exd5 8. Nc3 O-O 9. dxc5 ({The classical approach, though} 9. Bg5 {has been played more often.}) 9... d4 $6 {This is just a dubious line.} 10. Na4 Bf5 11. b4 $1 {Probably not the only move to take an advantage - but my favourite one!} Nxb4 $6 {Taking the b-pawn with the knight is dubious for Black.} 12. Nxd4 Be4 {Trying to exchange White's strong light-squared bishop.} 13. f3 Bc6 14. Nxc6 Nxc6 15. Be3 $16 {This is just a clear extra pawn for White.} *

