1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 (3... c5 4. O-O {is covered under 1.Nf3 d5 2.g3 c5 3.Bg2 g6 4.O-O}) 4. O-O (4. d4 {would transpose into very classical positions - which might be recommendable if you aren't satisfied with the lines that follow. Indeed, Black equalizes, but he should be smart and play precise moves.}) 4... c5 {This is also an interesting option for Black.} 5. d4 {This is my suggestion as I don't believe KIA plans like d3, Nbd2, e4, are of any danger for Black.} cxd4 6. Nxd4 Nf6 7. Nb3 $5 ({A challenging option.} 7. c4 O-O 8. cxd5 Nxd5 {transposes to 1.Nf3 Nf6 2.g3 g6 3.Bg2 Bg7 4.O-O O-O 5.c4 c5 6.d4 cxd4 7.Nxd4 d5 8.cxd5 Nxd5 , and is another possible try.}) 7... O-O 8. Nc3 e6 9. e4 {White strikes in the center and Black has no good way to meet it.} Nxe4 10. Nxe4 dxe4 11. Qxd8 (11. Bxe4 {allows Black to keep queens with} Qc7 {which I think is fine for him.}) 11... Rxd8 12. Bxe4 Nc6 13. c3 a5 $1 (13... e5 14. Bg2 {with Bg5 or Be3 to follow.}) (13... Ne5 {right away does not equalize:} 14. Nc5 Nc4 15. Bf4 $1 e5 {15...Nxb2? 16.Nxb7 $16} 16. Bg5 f6 17. Rfd1 $1 Bf5 18. b3 {with problems for Black.}) 14. a4 ({The most natural and best answer.} 14. Bg5 f6 15. Be3 a4 16. Nc5 f5 17. Bg2 a3 {should be fine for Black.}) 14... Ne5 $1 15. Bg5 (15. Nc5 $146 {is no longer convincing as after} Nc4 16. Bf4 Nxb2 17. Nxb7 Bxb7 18. Bxb7 {the a8-rook isn't trapped.} Ra7 $132) 15... Re8 $6 (15... f6 $1 {has never been played. After} 16. Be3 Nc4 17. Rfd1 Rxd1+ 18. Rxd1 Nxb2 19. Rd8+ Kf7 20. Nxa5 Ke7 $1 21. Rg8 {21.Nxb7 Bxb7 22.Rxa8 Bxa8 23.Bxa8 Nxa4=} Kf7 {Black gets a draw.}) 16. Rad1 Nc4 17. Bc1 e5 18. Nc5 Z0 (18... Bf8 {was played in Meier - Oparin, lichess. org 2020, and here after} 19. Nd7 $1 Be7 20. Rd5 $1 {White seems much better.}) *

