1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 (2... Bf5 3. Bg2 {will transpose.}) 3. Bg2 c6 4. O-O Bf5 (4... h6 {This prepares ...Bf5, making sure the bishop can hide on h7 if necessary.} 5. c4 Bf5 6. Qb3 Qb6 7. d3 {We are going to transpose into similar positions as the main line, where ...h6 has cost a tempo and hasn't been particularly useful.}) 5. c4 dxc4 6. Na3 b5 $2 {A bad move - but the only way to justify 5...dxc4? that otherwise just concedes the center for free.} 7. b3 cxb3 8. Qxb3 {This is just bad for Black.} e6 9. d3 $1 Z0 ({And Ne5 is coming, e.g.} 9... Bg6 10. Ne5 Nd5 11. Bb2 a6 12. Nc2 Ra7 13. a4 $16 {Skoberne - Gheng, Germany 2015. If 9.Ne5?! Be4 $132 Oparin - Tanenbaum, lichess.org 2020.}) *

