1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 c6 4. O-O Nbd7 {This is not a line to worry about.} 5. d4 e6 6. Nbd2 Bd6 $6 7. Re1 $1 {The best plan with the bishop on d6.} O-O ({White wants push e4, and for example} 7... Ne4 $2 {would lose to} 8. Nxe4 dxe4 9. Ng5 {because Black’s bishop isn’t on e7.}) 8. e4 dxe4 9. Nxe4 Nxe4 10. Rxe4 {And White is clearly better.} b6 11. c4 Bb7 12. Qc2 $1 {And now it’s Black’s chance to push …c5 but this move can't be played immediately…} Be7 (12... c5 13. Rxe6 $1 {This is the point with the bishop on d6 and not e7!} fxe6 14. Ng5 Nf6 15. Bxb7 cxd4 16. Be4 $16) 13. c5 $1 {A crucial move, causing Black concrete problems.} bxc5 14. dxc5 Nxc5 ({After} 14... Bxc5 15. Rh4 g6 16. Bh6 Re8 17. Rd1 {this is killing for White.}) 15. Rd4 $1 Qc8 16. Bg5 $1 {No rest for Black!} f6 17. Rh4 $1 g6 18. Bh6 Rf7 19. Re1 {With Bh3 to come and wonderful compensation for White.} *

