1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 c6 4. O-O Nbd7 {This is not a line to worry about.} 5. d4 e6 6. Nbd2 Be7 $1 7. c4 (7. Re1 O-O 8. e4 dxe4 9. Nxe4 Nxe4 10. Rxe4 b6 {would no longer be convincing for White: Black is in time to play ...Bb7 and ...c5.}) 7... O-O 8. Qc2 {We got an advantageous Catalan as Black has played …Nbd7 too early, and we will be able to push e2-e4 in wonderful conditions.} b6 9. e4 Bb7 $6 10. e5 Ne8 11. cxd5 cxd5 12. Re1 {This is a very, very good position for White, as several black pieces are very poorly placed. Stockfish 15, on a high depth, already gives White a +1 advantage.} Qc7 (12... Qc8 13. Qd1 a5 14. h4 Ba6 15. Nf1 b5 16. Bg5 $16 {Theodorou - Nguyen Ngoc Truong Son, chess.com 2023.}) 13. Qd1 a5 14. Nf1 Rc8 15. Bd2 $16 {This is another one-way street for White. If ... Qc2 White will trade queens and try to trap the rook with Bc3 and Ne3.} Z0 ({For instance,} 15... Qc2 16. Qxc2 Rxc2 17. Bc3 {, and if} Bb4 {to save the rook, now best is} 18. Bxb4 $1 {with the advantage, and not 18.Ne3 since after the exchange sacrifice 18...Rxc3 Black takes the rook back, 19.bxc3 Bxc3= 15.Ne3 Ba6 16.h4↑ Cheparinov - Piorun, Skopje 2019.}) *

