1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 (2... e6 {will transpose as the black knight will develop on f6 anyhow.}) 3. Bg2 e6 {Against this setup we'll go for a typical KIA setup.} 4. O-O Bd6 $6 {Only here we're changing our plan.} 5. c4 (5. d3 O-O 6. Nbd2 {would now allow} e5 {which I believe is fine for Black.}) 5... O-O 6. d4 $1 {We're transposing into a good variation of the Catalan for White.} c6 7. Nc3 Nbd7 8. Nd2 Z0 ({White will push e4 next, and has an excellent position. Actually, although around 400 games were played, this doesn't require more analysis: the opening has been a failure for Black. For example after} 8... Be7 9. e4 dxe4 10. Ndxe4 Nxe4 11. Nxe4 Nf6 {White can play} 12. Nc3 {or 12.Be3 , both with a nice advantage.}) *

