1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 e6 {Against this setup we'll go for a typical KIA setup.} 4. O-O Be7 5. d3 O-O 6. Nbd2 Nc6 $5 {A very decent move, I must admit!} 7. e4 {Unfortunately this does not lead to any advantage at all.} dxe4 (7... e5 $6 8. exd5 Nxd5 9. Re1 {and Black has concrete problems as} f6 {is met by} 10. d4 $1 exd4 11. Nb3 {10...Nxd4? loses a piece after 11.Nxd4 exd4 12.Bxd5+ Qxd5 13.Rxe7+-}) 8. dxe4 e5 9. Nc4 $5 (9. c3 a5 $1 10. Qc2 Be6 $1 11. Ng5 Bd7 12. Nc4 {and White's plan is to put his g5-knight back to f3 and the other one on e3.} Ng4 $1 13. Nf3 Be6 14. Ne3 Bc5 {and Black has equalize or even more - he's too active.}) 9... Qxd1 10. Rxd1 Nxe4 11. Nfxe5 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 {This is somehow light, but a bit unpleasant for Black.} Nd6 $1 (12... Nf6 13. Nc4 c6 14. c3 Nd5 15. Bxd5 cxd5 16. Ne3 Bc5 {occured in Giri - Aronian, 2015, and here after} 17. Rxd5 {I believe Black would have some work ahead to make to a draw.}) 13. a4 $5 (13. Nd3 Bf5 14. Bf4 {Mamedov - Kryvoruchko, Tornelo 2021.} Rad8 $146 {is just equal.}) 13... Bf5 (13... Bf6 14. Nd3 Rd8 15. a5 Bg4 16. Re1 {was unpleasant for Black in Amin - Nguyen, Warsaw 2021, 1-0.}) 14. Nd3 Rad8 15. a5 Bf6 16. Bf4 g5 $132 {As in the game Amin - Bacrot, Krasnaya Polyana 2021. I am afraid there is no improvement for White in this 7. e4 line.} *

