1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 (2... e6 {will transpose as the black knight will develop on f6 anyhow.}) 3. Bg2 e6 {Against this setup we'll go for a typical KIA setup.} 4. O-O Be7 5. d3 O-O 6. Nbd2 c5 7. e4 dxe4 {This is generally wrong when Black’s already pushed …c5. Indeed, he’ll have a choice between allowing e5-Ne4 or pushing …e5 himself, which creates a big hole on d5.} 8. dxe4 Nc6 9. Qe2 e5 10. Nc4 Qc7 11. c3 {Taking control of the d4-square. This is a better structure for White as Black has a hole on d5 and White does not have any weak spot.} *

