1. Nf3 c5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 (3. d4 $6 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. Bg2 Bg7 {does not give White time to transpose into lines seen under 1...Nf6 with 2...g6 and 5...c5, and the d4-knight is under attack.}) 3... d5 4. d4 cxd4 (4... Nf6 5. O-O {transposes into 1...d5 and 2... c5 lines.}) 5. Nxd4 e5 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. c4 Bb4+ $2 ({Now Black should play} 7... Nf6 {to transpose in 1.Nf3 Nf6 2.g3 c5 3.Bg2 Nc6 4.d4 cxd4 5.Nxd4 d5 6.c4 e5 7.Nxc6 bxc6 , else he'll get a bad position.}) (7... Be6 $6 8. Nc3 Nf6 {also transposes to the line reported on move seven, but into a bad version - with 8...Be6.}) 8. Nc3 $1 {The bishop on b4 is badly placed as cxd5 with the idea of ...cxd5 Qa4+ is a threat.} d4 {Starting a forced sequence.} 9. a3 Ba5 10. Bxc6+ Bd7 11. Qa4 Nf6 ({Black cannot play} 11... Bxc6 12. Qxc6+ Kf8 13. b4 {and White has a big advantage.}) 12. Bxd7+ Nxd7 13. b4 dxc3 ({Or} 13... Bc7 14. Nd5 {, where White has a bigger plus.}) 14. bxa5 O-O 15. Be3 {The c3-pawn will fall later, with a large advantage for White.} *

