1. Nf3 c5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 (3. d4 $6 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. Bg2 Bg7 {does not give White time to transpose into lines seen under 1...Nf6 with 2...g6 and 5...c5, and the d4-knight is under attack.}) 3... g6 (3... Nf6 {transposes to 1...Nf6 and 2... c5 lines.}) 4. c4 Bg7 5. Nc3 d6 ({•} 5... e5 {goes straight into the last chapter (1...c5 with 2...Nc6 and 3...e5), the Botvinnik System.}) ({•} 5... Nf6 6. d4 cxd4 7. Nxd4 O-O 8. O-O {transposes to 1...Nf6, 2...g6 and 5... c5 lines.}) 6. O-O h5 {Quite an aggressive reaction, but one that is definitely worth considering.} 7. Rb1 Nh6 8. a3 Nf5 9. Ng5 $146 a5 ({An interesting way to make} 9... h4 {bad, due to} 10. g4 {and ...h3 is 'legal' but defended by the g5-knight. Now, due to the hanging knight on c6 if Black moves his b-pawn, he needs one more time to manage to push ...b5. • 9.b4 h4 as in Jones, G (2665)-Le, Q (2709) chess.com 2022, 0-1 (33), is no drama, but not something I like to allow. • 9.h3 This is the typical way to prevent ...h4, as g4 would be a nasty answer when Black can't continue with ...h3, but it gives Black time to castle. 9...O-O 10.d3 Rb8 followed by ...a6 and ...b5.}) {As Black isn't in time to castle and counter d3, Bd2, b4 in time, this becomes the most natural reaction. Note that playing d3-Bd2 before playing b4 is a luxury. Playing b4 straight away is possible but then White cannot develop as smoothly due to the hanging knight on c3 if he goes d2-d3.} 10. d3 O-O 11. Bd2 Rb8 {The most logical move: one day Black would like to push ...b5 in one way or another.} 12. f4 $5 {A crazy idea which I thought of, first believing it can't be serious. I now believe it's the best move! White switches to aggressive mode and is even ready to give his bishop pair if Black goes ...Bd4+ and ...Ne3 for a few tempi in return.} e6 (12... Na7 13. e4 $1 Nd4 14. f5 $1 {and the attack starts.}) 13. e3 $5 {And Black is basically without a good move: next for White could be b4 just like it could be e3-e4 (e.g. if one of the black knights is demobilized) or g3-g4 to attack straight away.} *

