e goes} 15. exf7+ Rxf7 $2 16. Nb5 $1 {and Black is in serious trouble.}) 15. exd5 Nxd5 16. Nxc4 Bxc4 17. Qg4 Qf6 18. Kh1 $1 {This line isn't easy to handle as Black.} Qxf2 (18... Bb3 19. Ra3 h5 20. Qh3 Bc4 21. Ne4 Qf7 22. g4 {with the attack.}) 19. Bg5 Bxc3 20. bxc3 Qf5 21. Qh4 {With huge compensation.} *

