e goes} 15. exf7+ Rxf7 $2 16. Nb5 $1 {and Black is in serious trouble.}) 15. exd5 Nxd5 16. Nxc4 Nxc3 17. Qg4 $1 ({Critical!} 17. bxc3 Bxc4 18. Bxa8 Qxa8 {is unclear.}) 17... Qd4 18. Qxe6+ (18. Bf4 Bxc4 19. bxc3 Qxc3 20. Bxa8 Rxa8 {isn't clear.}) 18... Kh8 19. Nd6 Ne2+ (19... Qxf2+ $4 20. Kh1 {and Black is just lost! E.g.} Ne2 21. Be3 Qf6 22. Qxf6 Bxf6 23. Bxa8 Rxa8 24. a5 {and Black's position falls apart.}) 20. Rxe2 Bxe2 21. Qxe2 Qxd6 22. Bxa8 Z0 ({And after the obvious} 22... Rxa8 {, unfortunately, Black has equalized! Anyhow a super-challenging line for him!}) *

