{After 21...Qxb2 White's compensation is enormous, but apparently just for equality. At almost any moment Bh6+ will force a draw as black's pieces are heavily tied down.} 1. Nf3 c5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 g6 4. c4 Bg7 5. Nc3 e6 {A very solid line: Black wants to play ...Nge7 and ...d5 to take control (or at least neutralize) the center.} 6. d4 $5 {The old move - and most tricky one I believe.} (6. h4 $5 {is the newest fashion, but sadly, after spending lots of hours trying to make it work, after} h6 7. d4 {7.e3 Nge7 8.d4 cxd4 9.Nxd4 d5 10.cxd5 Nxd5 11.O-O O-O 12.Bd2 Nxd4 13.exd4 Ne7 doesn't lead to anything either.} cxd4 8. Nb5 d5 9. cxd5 exd5 10. O-O Nf6 {I had to conclude that having included h4 and ...h6 favored Black, as the g4-square is weak, when g5 is simply under control.}) 6... cxd4 7. Nb5 d5 8. cxd5 Qa5+ {One of the two possible moves for Black.} 9. Nd2 $1 ({The best try, I believe. After} 9. Qd2 Qxb5 10. dxc6 Ne7 $1 {I could not even find a good continuation for White.}) 9... exd5 10. Nd6+ Kf8 11. O-O ({Critical. I've also checked} 11. Nxc8 Rxc8 12. O-O {but after} Nf6 13. Nb3 Qb6 14. e3 h5 $1 15. exd4 Bh6 16. Bxh6+ {it seemed pretty clear that Black had equalized in Iturrizaga, E (2607)-Pulvett, D (2476) Benasque 2021, when a draw was immediately agreed.}) 11... Be6 {One of the three natural moves.} 12. e4 $146 ({Oye! Let's go for a mess!} 12. Nf3 Qb4 13. Bf4 h6 {was played in Wojtaszek, R (2676) -Dominguez Perez, L (2739) Baku 2023, ½-½ (44), when I am not convinced White can really create problems.}) (12. Nxb7 Qb6 13. Nd6 $2 Rd8 {just loses the knight.}) 12... dxe3 (12... dxe4 $4 13. N2xe4 {with ideas like Nxb7 or Ng5 is just horrific for Black (the eval is already +2.5!).}) 13. Nb3 $1 ({The point. Let's give another pawn!} 13. fxe3 $2 Qb4 {just traps the d6-knight.}) 13... Qb4 14. Bxe3 b6 (14... Qxd6 $4 15. Bc5 {wins the queen.}) 15. Nc5 $5 {Huh?} bxc5 16. Bxd5 Nge7 ({Or} 16... Rd8 17. Bxe6 Nge7 $1 {transposing.}) 17. Bxe6 Rd8 ({Only move!} 17... fxe6 $4 18. Qf3+ Nf5 19. Qxc6) 18. Rc1 c4 {Only move again!} 19. Nxf7 $1 Rxd1 20. Rfxd1 Bf6 $1 21. Rxc4 ({Or} 21. Bh6+ Bg7 22. Be3 Bf6) 21... Z0 *

