1. Nf3 c5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 e5 {With ...g6 to follow, this is called the Botvinnik system.} 4. c4 (4. e4 Nf6 5. O-O {would transpose into 1.Nf3 Nf6 2.g3 c5 3.Bg2 Nc6 4.O-O!? e5 5.e4 .}) 4... f5 $6 {This aggressive move is too weakening for Black.} 5. Nc3 Nf6 (5... e4 $2 6. Ng1 $1 {followed by d3.}) 6. d3 d6 7. Rb1 Be7 8. a3 a5 (8... O-O 9. b4 {just looks great for White.}) 9. Bg5 Be6 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. Nd5 Bxd5 12. cxd5 Ne7 13. Nd2 {With either a4/Nc4 or e4 to follow soon. We followed the game Ponkratov - Niemann, chess.com 2022.} *

