1. Nf3 c5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 e5 {With ...g6 to follow, this is called the Botvinnik system.} 4. c4 (4. e4 Nf6 5. O-O {would transpose into 1.Nf3 Nf6 2.g3 c5 3.Bg2 Nc6 4.O-O!? e5 5.e4 .}) 4... g6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. a3 Nge7 (6... d6 7. O-O {will soon transpose.}) 7. d3 (7. O-O O-O 8. Ne1 d6 9. Nc2 Be6 10. Ne3 Qd7 $1 11. Ned5 Bh3 {isn't convincing for White at all. Radjabov - Vachier Lagrave, Terme Catez 2021.}) (7. b4 {allows} d5 $1 {with huge complications that do not favor White. 1-0 Lagarde - L'Ami, Chennai 2022.}) 7... O-O ({Again,} 7... d6 8. Rb1 {will soon transpose.}) 8. Rb1 {The simplest plan, going for b4, and one of the best tries for White in my opinion.} d5 9. cxd5 Nxd5 10. Nxd5 Qxd5 11. O-O {This is pleasant for White, as Black does not have time for ...Be6 and ...Qd7 due to Ng5.} *

