1. Nf3 c5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 e5 {With ...g6 to follow, this is called the Botvinnik system.} 4. c4 (4. e4 Nf6 5. O-O {would transpose into 1.Nf3 Nf6 2.g3 c5 3.Bg2 Nc6 4.O-O!? e5 5.e4 .}) 4... g6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. a3 Nge7 (6... d6 7. O-O {will soon transpose.}) 7. d3 (7. O-O O-O 8. Ne1 d6 9. Nc2 Be6 10. Ne3 Qd7 $1 11. Ned5 Bh3 {isn't convincing for White at all. Radjabov - Vachier Lagrave, Terme Catez 2021.}) (7. b4 {allows} d5 $1 {with huge complications that do not favor White. 1-0 Lagarde - L'Ami, Chennai 2022.}) 7... O-O ({Again,} 7... d6 8. Rb1 {will soon transpose.}) 8. Rb1 {The simplest plan, going for b4, and one of the best tries for White in my opinion.} a5 (8... d6 9. b4 {is just nice for White - it definitely makes sense to stop b2-b4.}) 9. O-O d6 10. b3 $5 {A good try - changing plan and forgetting about b2-b4 now that Black has weakened himself with ...a5.} (10. Ne1 Be6 11. Nc2 d5 {is unsatisfying.}) 10... Rb8 11. Bb2 h6 {The most natural move: Black wants to play ...Be6 without allowing Ng5.} 12. Nd2 Be6 13. Nd5 {Of course we should stop ...d5.} b5 14. e3 Qd7 15. Re1 {We want to free the f1-square mostly to play Qf1 and meet ...Bg4 with Qf1. We do not want to commit with f3 or f4 yet, as we may decide to prepare it better.} (15. Qe2 Bg4 $1 16. f3 Be6 {with ideas like ...a4 or ...bxc4 and some sacrifices on b2 was fine for Black in Thybo - Korley, Skanderborg 2023.}) 15... Bf5 16. Qe2 $5 (16. Qc2 Be6 17. f4 {is very much playable as well: Lagarde - Saduakassova, Sitges 2019.}) 16... Bg4 (16... Bh3 $2 17. Bxh3 $1 Qxh3 18. Nxe7+ Nxe7 19. cxb5 $1 Rxb5 20. d4 {is just terrible for Black.}) 17. Qf1 {And Black's bishop on g4 is a target for White's kingside expansion. Next might be h3, or Nc3 to provoke ...b4, try to open the a-file and go Ra1.} *

