1. Nf3 f5 {Black plays in the spirit of the Dutch Defense. We will try to take advantage of the fact that white has yet to play d4.} 2. d3 $5 {White wants to play e4 which is very different to the main lines of the Dutch Defence where white is already committed to d4.} d6 $5 {Black also intends to fight for the center.} 3. e4 $1 e5 4. Nc3 $1 c5 $6 {Black wants to stop a possible d3-d4, but this is simply too much. Black hasn’t developed a single piece yet and White will take advantage of it to take over the initiative.} 5. g3 $1 Be7 6. Bh3 $1 {A clever plan to force Black to weaken his position even more.} fxe4 (6... g6 $2 7. exf5 gxf5 8. Nh4 $1 {+-}) 7. Bxc8 Qxc8 8. dxe4 {Black's hole on d5 is reaaaaally ugly!} Nf6 $6 9. Bg5 $1 O-O 10. Nh4 {There's another weak spot on f5!} g6 11. Nd5 Qd8 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. Ng2 $16 {White is living the dream on the light squares, especially the d5-square, and Black is left without counterplay. Fressinet - Vaisser, Haguenau 2013.} *

