1. Nf3 f5 {Black plays in the spirit of the Dutch Defense. We will try to take advantage of the fact that white has yet to play d4.} 2. d3 $5 {White wants to play e4 which is very different to the main lines of the Dutch Defence where white is already committed to d4.} d6 $5 {Black also intends to fight for the center.} 3. e4 $1 e5 4. Nc3 $1 c5 $6 {Black wants to stop a possible d3-d4, but this is simply too much. Black hasn’t developed a single piece yet and White will take advantage of it to take over the initiative.} 5. g3 $1 Nc6 6. Nh4 $1 (6. Bh3 $5 fxe4 7. Bxc8 Qxc8 8. dxe4 {and with such a nice square on d5, White can only be better. For example} Qh3 9. Nd5 O-O-O 10. Qd3 Nge7 11. c3 {followed by Be3 and O-O-O.}) 6... fxe4 7. dxe4 Be7 8. Bc4 $1 Bxh4 9. gxh4 Nd4 10. Bg5 Qd7 11. Nd5 b5 12. Be2 $16 {White wants c3 next, or Bg4 if Black moves his c8-bishop, with a clear advantage.} *

