1. Nf3 f5 {Black plays in the spirit of the Dutch Defense. We will try to take advantage of the fact that white has yet to play d4.} 2. d3 $5 {White wants to play e4 which is very different to the main lines of the Dutch Defence where white is already committed to d4.} d6 $5 {Black also intends to fight for the center.} 3. e4 $1 e5 4. Nc3 $1 Nc6 {The only playable line.} 5. exf5 Bxf5 $6 {This simple recapture isn’t good. As we’ll see, Black needs to be more ingenious if he wants a playable game.} 6. d4 $1 {White takes over the initiative.} Nf6 $6 {Refusing to enter complications only makes Black’s position even worse.} 7. Bb5 $1 e4 $2 {7...e4 fails for tactical reasons, as we are about to see.} 8. d5 $1 {This doesn’t work for Black at all.} exf3 ({Attacking the bishop with} 8... a6 {doesn't solve Black's problems. After} 9. Bxc6+ $5 bxc6 10. Nd4 Bd7 11. dxc6 {White is winning.}) 9. dxc6 $1 bxc6 10. Bxc6+ Bd7 11. Bxa8 Qxa8 12. Qxf3 {White is an exchange up and is just winning.} *

