1. Nf3 f5 {Black plays in the spirit of the Dutch Defense. We will try to take advantage of the fact that white has yet to play d4.} 2. d3 $5 {White wants to play e4 which is very different to the main lines of the Dutch Defence where white is already committed to d4.} d6 $5 {Black also intends to fight for the center.} 3. e4 $1 e5 4. Nc3 $1 Nc6 {The only playable line.} 5. exf5 Bxf5 $6 {This simple recapture isn’t good. As we’ll see, Black needs to be more ingenious if he wants a playable game.} 6. d4 $1 {White takes over the initiative.} Nxd4 (6... Nb4 $6 7. Bb5+ c6 8. Ba4 $16 {White simply defends the c2-pawn and the black knight feels very lonely on b4.}) (6... e4 $6 7. d5 exf3 8. dxc6 bxc6 9. Qxf3 $16 {and White enjoys a nice advantage.}) 7. Nxd4 exd4 8. Qxd4 Bxc2 $146 {This is way too risky.} 9. Bc4 Qf6 (9... c6 10. O-O Nf6 11. Re1+ Be7 12. Bg5) 10. Qd2 Bg6 11. O-O c6 (11... O-O-O {?} 12. Nd5 Qh4 13. Bb3 Nf6 14. Qa5 Nxd5 15. Bxd5) 12. Re1+ Be7 13. Qd1 $1 O-O-O (13... d5 14. Bxd5 $1 O-O-O 15. Be3 $1 cxd5 16. Bxa7 {with a crushing attack (+4 for White!).}) 14. Be3 {Black is busted.} *

