1. Nf3 f5 {Black plays in the spirit of the Dutch Defense. We will try to take advantage of the fact that white has yet to play d4.} 2. d3 $5 {White wants to play e4 which is very different to the main lines of the Dutch Defence where white is already committed to d4.} d6 $5 {Black also intends to fight for the center.} 3. e4 $1 e5 4. Nc3 $1 Nc6 {The only playable line.} 5. exf5 Nge7 $5 {By far the best line for Black, in the whole 2... d6 variation.} 6. g4 $5 {Let's take a look at three possible alternatives for White.} ({A)} 6. f6 $6 gxf6 7. d4 d5 $1 {$146} 8. dxe5 fxe5 9. Ng5 Bf5 $132) ({B)} 6. d4 exd4 7. Nxd4 Nxd4 8. Qxd4 Nxf5 {8...Bxf5? 9.Bg5 $16} 9. Qe4+ Qe7 {9...Be7? 10.g4! Nh4 11.Nd5 $16} 10. Bd3 Qxe4+ 11. Nxe4 {is only a very modest plus for White.}) ({C)} 6. Nh4 $6 Nxf5 $1 7. Qh5+ g6 8. Nxg6 Ng7 9. Qh4 Qxh4 10. Nxh4 Nd4 11. Kd1 Be7 {gives Black fine compensation.}) 6... h5 7. gxh5 $1 {I really like this line for White!} Nxf5 (7... Bxf5 8. Nh4 Qd7 9. Nxf5 Nxf5 10. Bh3 $1 O-O-O 11. Qg4 $1 Ncd4 12. Be3 $1 Qc6 13. O-O-O {seems great for White.}) 8. Rg1 $1 Ncd4 (8... d5 9. Bg5 $1 Qd7 10. Bd2 $5 {followed by Bh3, Qe2, and Black has concrete problems.}) (8... Qe7 9. Ng5 $1 {and Nd5 will create problems.}) 9. Nxd4 $146 Nxd4 (9... exd4 $2 10. Qe2+ Qe7 11. Nd5 Qxe2+ 12. Bxe2) 10. h6 $1 {And with Qh5 as a threat, Black has concrete problems to solve.} Qf6 $5 11. Be2 $1 Nxe2 (11... Bf5 12. hxg7 Bxg7 13. Bh5+ Kd7 14. Nd5 Qf8 15. c3) 12. Qxe2 gxh6 13. Bd2 Bf5 14. O-O-O O-O-O 15. f4 exf4 16. Qf2 {White's position is very promising.} *

