1. Nf3 f5 {Black plays in the spirit of the Dutch Defense. We will try to take advantage of the fact that white has yet to play d4.} 2. d3 $5 {White wants to play e4 which is very different to the main lines of the Dutch Defence where white is already committed to d4.} Nc6 $1 {One of the two playable moves - together with 2... d6.} 3. d4 $5 {We give one tempo away, but prevent Black from pushing ...e5 and the knight on c6 turns out to be misplaced.} e6 4. g3 Nf6 5. Bg2 d6 6. c4 e5 7. d5 $5 Ne7 8. Ng5 $1 {For concrete reasons, White is in time to create problems.} h6 (8... g6 9. Nc3 Bg7 10. O-O O-O 11. Qb3 $1 h6 12. Ne6 Bxe6 13. dxe6 {and the b7-pawn is hanging, else Rd1 and c5 is coming.}) 9. Ne6 Bxe6 10. dxe6 Qc8 11. Nc3 c6 (11... Qxe6 $6 12. Bxb7 Rd8 13. Nd5 $16) 12. Qb3 $1 (12. Qxd6 Ng6 13. Qd1 {may also lead to a slight plus.}) 12... b6 13. e4 Qxe6 14. exf5 Qxf5 15. O-O {White has compensation on the light squares and Black's king is very unsafe.} *

