1. Nf3 f5 {Black plays in the spirit of the Dutch Defense. We will try to take advantage of the fact that white has yet to play d4.} 2. d3 $5 {White wants to play e4 which is very different to the main lines of the Dutch Defence where white is already committed to d4.} Nc6 $1 {One of the two playable moves - together with 2... d6.} 3. d4 $5 {We give one tempo away, but prevent Black from pushing ...e5 and the knight on c6 turns out to be misplaced.} e6 4. g3 Nf6 5. Bg2 Be7 6. c4 O-O 7. d5 $5 ({I believe this forcing move leads to a small advantage.} 7. O-O d6 8. d5 Ne5 9. Nd4 Nxc4 $1 10. dxe6 d5 $1 {is not so clear.}) 7... Bb4+ (7... Na5 8. Qd3 b6 9. Nc3 Bb4 10. O-O Bb7 11. Bd2 {is just good for White.}) 8. Bd2 Bxd2+ 9. Qxd2 Ne4 10. Qd1 Ne7 11. O-O {Here Black is worse off unless he can come up with something concrete. But this does not seem to be the case.} exd5 12. cxd5 c6 13. d6 $1 Ng6 14. Nc3 Z0 ({And things seem to work for White, for instance} 14... Qf6 15. Nxe4 fxe4 16. Nd2 Qxd6 17. Qb3+ $1 Kh8 18. Nxe4 Qe7 19. Rae1 d5 20. Nd2 {followed by e4, or f4 ad then e4, with a nice advantage.}) *

