1. Nf3 f5 {Black plays in the spirit of the Dutch Defense. We will try to take advantage of the fact that white has yet to play d4.} 2. d3 $5 {White wants to play e4 which is very different to the main lines of the Dutch Defence where white is already committed to d4.} Nc6 $1 {One of the two playable moves - together with 2... d6.} 3. d4 $5 {We give one tempo away, but prevent Black from pushing ...e5 and the knight on c6 turns out to be misplaced.} e6 4. g3 Nf6 5. Bg2 Be7 6. c4 O-O 7. d5 $5 ({I believe this forcing move leads to a small advantage.} 7. O-O d6 8. d5 Ne5 9. Nd4 Nxc4 $1 10. dxe6 d5 $1 {is not so clear.}) 7... exd5 8. cxd5 Nb4 9. Nc3 c6 {Black needs to play this move, challenging White in the center, otherwise the whole position is awful.} 10. Ng5 $1 h6 11. h4 $1 Qb6 (11... hxg5 $2 12. hxg5 {turns to a nightmare for Black as} Nfxd5 $2 {loses to} 13. Nxd5 Nxd5 14. Bxd5+ cxd5 15. Qxd5+ Rf7 16. g6) 12. O-O $3 {The start of an awesome variation} hxg5 (12... Nbxd5 13. Nxd5 cxd5 14. Bxd5+ Nxd5 15. Qxd5+ Kh8 16. Nh3 {followed by Nf4 is excellent for White.}) 13. d6 $1 Bxd6 (13... Bd8 14. hxg5 Nh7 15. g6 Nf6 16. a3 Na6 17. b4 {is just horrific for Black: look at ALL the black pieces!}) 14. Qxd6 Nc2 (14... gxh4 $2 15. Be3 Qa5 16. Bc5) 15. hxg5 $1 Ne8 16. Qd3 $1 Nxa1 17. Qc4+ $1 {Just wow!} d5 (17... Kh7 18. Qh4+ Kg6 19. e4 {just wins.}) 18. Nxd5 cxd5 19. Bxd5+ Kh7 20. Be3 Qa6 21. Qh4+ Kg6 22. Bf3 Kf7 23. g6+ {What a line!} *

